RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 54. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAY STRONG settled into the second flight and trekked the two path through the opening half, swung to three wide at upper stretch, locked into a heated stretch duel, and won the nod at wire for the score. J R ORCHESTRATE was unurried through the opening half and trailed the field through the first two calls, angled out to five wide at upper stretch, dueled the length of the homestretch, and was nipped by slimmest of margins at the finish. HOMEGROWN LEGEND saved ground through the first turn while giving case from the second flight, closed the gap on leader along the backstretch, gained brief command near the quarter pole, but could not fend off the dueling duo in final furlong. GOSPEL GRAYSTONE rushed from outset and established a comfortable lead onto the backstretch, was challenged near the half pole, relished command nearing the quarter pole, and weakened in the crucial stages of contest.

ENTRY.NAME: Homegrown Legend
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, brief lead near quarter pole, couldnt fend

ENTRY.NAME: Stay Strong
ENTRY.COMMENT: two path trip, three wide upper, won nod

ENTRY.NAME: J R Orchestrate
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, five wide upper, dueled, nipped

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED RIVER WITCH hustled from outset and led the field into the homestretch, was headed near the eighth pole, and refused to lose the stretch duel for the score. ITSONLYMONEYHONEY stalked the pacesetter through the opening half while saving ground, locked into a stretch duel t top of lane, but was outdueled. PAYDIEM chased the pacesetter from a three wide stance, was within striking distance at upper stretch, but proved no match for top pair in final furlong. ORTS DREAM gave chase from a three path pose around the first turn and along the backstretch before angling wide at upper and stretch and lacking a needed rally to improve placing. LIL DITTY'S KITTY was reserved in the early stages, tucked to save ground midway through the opening bend, maintained that line into the homestretch, but lacked a rail rally to improve position. FOREIGN CREATION trailed from outset and was no factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Orts Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: three path, wide upper, no gain

ENTRY.NAME: Red River Witch
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, refused to lose stretch duel

ENTRY.NAME: Paydiem
ENTRY.OWNER: Covey Seth and Caldwell J R
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide, no match for top pair

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 14400. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since February 2 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered Fo r $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXCETERA stalked the pacesetter along the backstretch, advanced to be in concert for the lead at upper stretch, locked into a stretch duel and kicked clear in final sixteenth for the victory. MARIA ELENA Y. G zoomed from outset and led the field into the turn, was on even terms through the bend, headed at upper stretch, then failed to match strides with eventual winner in final sixteenth. DIXIELAND CANDY settled into the second flight, chased the pacesetting duo around the bend from a two path stance, and bested the rest while proving no match for top pair. GOSPEL CARLOTTA came away awkwardly, chased rivals into homestretch and failed to gain on leaders in closing strides. J LOVE was unhurried, trailed the field, traveled wide and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Maria Elena Y. G
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, headed upper, unable to match stride

ENTRY.NAME: Excetera
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, in concert upper, kicked clear

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since February 2 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $ 4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHE'S FIRE AND ICE pressed te pace from a two path stance, was in concert with that rival at upper stretch, then inched clear in final sixteenth for the score. BID FOR POWER rushed from outset and led the field through the half from a ground saving stance, was on even terms at the top of lane, and gave way to that rival in the stretch duel. STAYTHIRSTYMYAMIGO established a ground saving stance and settled into the second flight through the opening half, maintained the inside line into the homestretch and got up for show. STRONG WOMAN hustled from outset to press the pace from a three wide pose, rated close up at upper stretch, then failed to sustain the bid in closing stages. KIMBELL'S STRATEGY failed to threaten from a back rated stance. FETCHING FURY rated back and was never involved or near the top three.

ENTRY.NAME: Bid for Power
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace inside, gave way in duel

ENTRY.NAME: Strong Woman
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide journey, unable to sustain bid

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALI stalked the pacesetter from a two path pose along eh backstretch, advanced to be on even terms through the closing turn, locked into a stretch duel and won the nod at wire. FREE SPIRITED showed reserve in early going, advanced on the leaders inside the half pole, rated three wide at upper stretch, and was outdueled in final furlong. CREES VALENTYME settled into the second flight around the opening bend, saved ground through the half, and finished willingly for the show. SHEZONEZESTREET saved ground from a back rated stance through the opening half before angling out at upper stretch to no avail. SCRAPPY PATCH was unhurried and chased rivals from a back rated pose before passing tiring foe in late strides. MUSTANGMAGNA trekked wide shortly after the start, gained command into the backstretch, rated close up as the inner most rival at upper stretch, then eclipsed in closing stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Shezonezestreet
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, angled out upper to no avail

ENTRY.NAME: Crees Valentyme
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside second flight, willingly for show

ENTRY.NAME: Cali
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked two path, best in stretch duel

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Purse 30000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Multiple Winners Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRAZY LOVER showed interest in early command and set pace in concert from between rivals, locked into a stretch duel at upper stretch and proved best in the end. DOCTOR TINK rated close up shortly after start, trekked three wide amongst the leaders around the bend, was on even terms at upper strtch, but was outdueled in final sixteenth. CINCO STEVE pressed the pace as the widest of four rivals along the backstretch and through the turn before finishing evenly to secure the show. MIRANDEN came away alertly and set the pace in tandem as the inner most rival of four abreast, rated close up at upper stretch, and gave way to dueling duo in final stages. DANCING DEVIL lacked a needed rally after trailing rivals and giving chase from an inside stance.

ENTRY.NAME: Miranden
ENTRY.OWNER: B and S Racing (Bozarth and Smith)

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 43. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TUATHA gained command on first stride, saved ground throughout and never relished for a gate to wire score. SEATTLE WILDCAT broke alertly and trekked close up while three wide along the backstretch and around the bend, then finished a clear second but was no match for winner in closing stages. INDIAN ACES pressed the early pace from a two path stance, tucked to the inside near the quarter pole, then weakened along the inside in the final furlong. TOTAL RUSH showed reserve and rated well back into the turn before improving position in the late going. COMPETITIVE SPIRIT was unhurried early, advanced on leaders as the widest of all rivals around the bend, but tired in late strides. FLASHY GAIL failed to respond to urging after stalking the pace from a four wide pose in the opening half.

ENTRY.NAME: Indian Aces
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed two path, tucked near quarter pole, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Seattle Wildcat
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up three wide, no match late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 81. Allowance Purse 27600. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EARS TO ME showed reserve through the opening half, was roused inside the half pole and advanced on the leaders with a wide trip around closing bend before drawing clear of all challengers in final sixteenth. KODALINE settled into mid pack and chased the front runners from a two path pose, angled out near the quarter pole, and finished willingly to procure the place. DOMINANT OKIE stalked the early pacesetter from a four wide stance, rated close up three wide at upper stretch, but couldnt fend off the rally of eventual winner in closing strides. HOPGUN saved ground while giving chase from the second flight, swung three wide at upper stretch, tucked to rail near the three sixteenths pole, but lacked a rail rally in final furlong. DENS DEVILLE lacked a late bid after pressing the pace from between rivals and rating close up at upper stretch. PAPA BILL flashed early foot and led the field through the opening half while saving ground before tiring in the late going. CAPTAIN COMEBACK trailed the field through the opening turn, closed gap on leaders nearing the half pole, then faded in homestretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: inside second flight,three wide tucked three sixteenths, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Ears to Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, roused inside half pole, wide upper, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Captain Comeback
ENTRY.COMMENT: closed gap near half pole, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Dominant Okie
ENTRY.COMMENT: wide journey, couldnt fend off rally foe

ENTRY.NAME: Kodaline
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled mid pack, angled out quarter pole, second best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 9 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: JACKS SPRING BREAK stalked the frontrunner from a three path pose for the opening half, rated on front end at top of the lane and kicked clear in final furlong. NOMOREMRNICEGUY showed reserve through the opening bend, closed gap on leaders along the backstretch, was in tight nearing the midway point, trekked wide at upper stretch and finished with good late kick to procure the place. WAVERUNNER settled into a three wide pose around the opening turn, advanced on leaders along the backstretch, rated three wide and within striking distance at upper stretch, then finished evenly to hold the show. GOT MOJO flashed early speed and led the field onto and along the backstretch before giving way to closing rivals near the three eighths pole. LIMBO'S PROMISE pressed the early pace from a two path pose, gained brief command near the midway point, then retreated along the rail in closing strides. JOHN ALLEN settled in behind the leaders while establishing a ground saving stance, maintained that line throughout and was no threat in the end. CHOCOLATEICECREAM trailed from outset and passed tiring foe in late going. TARUCA failed to menace while giving chase from a two path position.
